Package: bootabc
Title: Bootstrap Confidence Intervals for Online Experiments
Version: 0.9.5
Authors@R:
    person("First", "Last", , "first.last@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Computes bootstrap confidence intervals for the key performance
    indicators (KPIs) of online controlled experiments (A/B tests), from data
    aggregated to one row per customer. Supports compound KPIs defined as ratios
    of sums, such as spend per active day, comparisons between variants (lift and
    difference), and bias-corrected and accelerated ('BCa') intervals. Variance
    can be reduced with pre-experiment data using the 'CUPED' method of Deng, Xu,
    Kohavi and Walker (2013) <doi:10.1145/2433396.2433413>. Resampling runs in a
    streaming 'C++' kernel.
